The so-called Millennials are taking serious strain, with many struggling to pay their student debt. LONDON - Britain is one of the world's richest countries, but it also has some financial troubles. The so-called Millennials are taking serious strain, with many struggling to pay their student debt. READ: Millennials choose car sharing over ownership Recent research by the Institute for Fiscal Studies shows house prices in England have risen by 173 percent since 1997, while average pay for 25 to 34-year-olds has increased by just 19 percent in that period. When it comes to buying a home, many young people in Britain find it hard to get on the property ladder, despite government schemes like help to buy.